## Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1-3)

### Week 1: Environment Setup & Core Infrastructure

**Objectives:**
- Set up development environment
- Establish project structure
- Implement basic encryption primitives

**Tasks:**
1. **Day 1-2: Project Setup**
   - [ ] Initialize Git repository
   - [ ] Set up Python virtual environment
   - [ ] Install dependencies from requirements.txt
   - [ ] Configure development tools (Black, Flake8, MyPy)
   - [ ] Set up CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions)

2. **Day 3-4: Core Cryptography**
   - [ ] Implement AES-256-GCM encryption wrapper
   - [ ] Implement PBKDF2 key derivation (100k iterations)
   - [ ] Test encryption/decryption with various key sizes
   - [ ] Verify prefix-keeping property for incremental updates
   - [ ] Write unit tests for crypto primitives

3. **Day 5-7: Basic Vault Structure**
   - [ ] Design vault data structure (metadata, accounts, etc.)
   - [ ] Implement vault serialization/deserialization
   - [ ] Create basic password entry CRUD operations
   - [ ] Implement vault versioning system
   - [ ] Write integration tests

**Deliverables:**
- ‚úÖ Working encryption/decryption system
- ‚úÖ Basic vault data structure
- ‚úÖ Test suite with >80% coverage
- ‚úÖ Documentation for core APIs

**Success Metrics:**
- All unit tests passing
- Encryption/decryption performance < 10ms
- Zero memory leaks in crypto code

---

### Week 2: Tokenizer & Basic Transformer

**Objectives:**
- Implement custom tokenizer for passwords
- Build initial Transformer model
- Validate model architecture

**Tasks:**
1. **Day 1-2: Tokenizer Implementation**
   - [ ] Implement VaultTokenizer class
   - [ ] Create vocabulary (95 ASCII + special tokens)
   - [ ] Add encode/decode functions
   - [ ] Implement vault-specific encoding (with <SEP>)
   - [ ] Test edge cases (empty passwords, special characters)

2. **Day 3-5: Transformer Architecture**
   - [ ] Implement PositionalEncoding module
   - [ ] Build VaultTransformer model (decoder-only)
   - [ ] Configure model: 768 dim, 12 layers, 12 heads
   - [ ] Implement causal attention masking
   - [ ] Test forward pass with dummy data

3. **Day 6-7: Model Testing & Validation**
   - [ ] Test model on synthetic data
   - [ ] Verify parameter count (~85M)
   - [ ] Test generation capabilities
   - [ ] Profile memory usage
   - [ ] Optimize for inference

**Deliverables:**
- ‚úÖ VaultTokenizer with full test coverage
- ‚úÖ VaultTransformer model (trainable)
- ‚úÖ Model documentation
- ‚úÖ Benchmark results

**Success Metrics:**
- Tokenizer handles all ASCII printable characters
- Model runs on both CPU and GPU
- Memory footprint < 1GB
- Forward pass < 100ms for 50-token sequence

---

### Week 3: Encoder Implementation

**Objectives:**
- Implement IS-PMTE encoder
- Integrate with Transformer model
- Validate encoding/decoding correctness

**Tasks:**
1. **Day 1-3: Core Encoder**
   - [ ] Implement HoneyEncoder class
   - [ ] Add encode_vault method (passwords ‚Üí seed)
   - [ ] Add decode_seed method (seed ‚Üí passwords)
   - [ ] Implement interval_to_seed (inverse sampling)
   - [ ] Implement seed_to_character (decoding)

2. **Day 4-5: Incremental Updates**
   - [ ] Implement encode_incremental method
   - [ ] Verify prefix-keeping property
   - [ ] Test with various vault sizes
   - [ ] Optimize for performance

3. **Day 6-7: Integration & Testing**
   - [ ] Integrate encoder with Transformer model
   - [ ] Test end-to-end encoding/decoding
   - [ ] Verify decoy generation quality
   - [ ] Profile performance bottlenecks
   - [ ] Write comprehensive test suite

**Deliverables:**
- ‚úÖ Complete HoneyEncoder implementation
- ‚úÖ Incremental update support
- ‚úÖ Integration tests
- ‚úÖ Performance benchmarks

**Success Metrics:**
- Encoding/decoding correctness: 100%
- Decoy vaults look realistic (manual review)
- Performance: < 1s for 20-password vault
- Zero encoding/decoding errors

