## Phase 2: Model Training (Weeks 4-7)

### Week 4: Data Collection & Preparation

**Objectives:**
- Collect/aggregate password datasets
- Clean and preprocess data
- Create vault training set

**Tasks:**
1. **Day 1-2: Data Sources**
   - [ ] Identify ethical password datasets (breach compilations)
   - [ ] Download publicly available datasets
   - [ ] Verify data licensing and ethics
   - [ ] Document data sources

2. **Day 3-5: Data Cleaning**
   - [ ] Parse datasets into unified format
   - [ ] Remove duplicates and invalid entries
   - [ ] Filter non-ASCII passwords
   - [ ] Normalize password formats
   - [ ] Validate email addresses for aggregation

3. **Day 6-7: Vault Aggregation**
   - [ ] Group passwords by user email
   - [ ] Create vault dataset (target: 1M+ vaults)
   - [ ] Split into train/val/test (70/15/15)
   - [ ] Generate statistics and distribution analysis
   - [ ] Export to efficient format (HDF5 or Parquet)

**Deliverables:**
- ‚úÖ Clean password dataset (millions of passwords)
- ‚úÖ Vault dataset (1M+ vaults)
- ‚úÖ Data statistics report
- ‚úÖ Ethical review document

**Success Metrics:**
- Dataset size: >1M vaults
- Data quality: <1% invalid entries
- Distribution matches real-world usage
- Ethical sourcing verified

---

### Week 5-6: Model Training

**Objectives:**
- Train Transformer model on vault data
- Optimize hyperparameters
- Achieve high-quality decoy generation

**Tasks:**
1. **Week 5, Day 1-3: Training Setup**
   - [ ] Implement VaultDataset class
   - [ ] Create DataLoader with proper batching
   - [ ] Set up training configuration
   - [ ] Configure optimizer (AdamW)
   - [ ] Set up learning rate scheduler
   - [ ] Initialize logging and monitoring

2. **Week 5, Day 4-7: Initial Training**
   - [ ] Start training on 100k vault subset
   - [ ] Monitor loss curves
   - [ ] Validate on held-out set
   - [ ] Adjust hyperparameters
   - [ ] Generate sample decoy vaults
   - [ ] Evaluate decoy quality (manual review)

3. **Week 6, Day 1-5: Full Training**
   - [ ] Train on full dataset (1M+ vaults)
   - [ ] Run for 5 epochs (~8 hours on GPU)
   - [ ] Save checkpoints every epoch
   - [ ] Monitor validation loss
   - [ ] Implement early stopping
   - [ ] Log training metrics to TensorBoard

4. **Week 6, Day 6-7: Model Evaluation**
   - [ ] Evaluate on test set
   - [ ] Generate 1000 decoy vaults
   - [ ] Manual quality assessment
   - [ ] Calculate perplexity
   - [ ] Compare to baseline models
   - [ ] Document results

**Deliverables:**
- ‚úÖ Trained Transformer model
- ‚úÖ Training logs and metrics
- ‚úÖ Model checkpoints
- ‚úÖ Evaluation report

**Success Metrics:**
- Validation loss converges
- Decoy vaults indistinguishable (manual review)
- Model perplexity < 5.0
- Generation diversity high

---

### Week 7: Model Optimization & Export

**Objectives:**
- Optimize model for production
- Export to ONNX format
- Benchmark performance

**Tasks:**
1. **Day 1-3: Optimization**
   - [ ] Implement model quantization (INT8)
   - [ ] Reduce model size with pruning
